public class GraphArchive extends com.telenav.kivakit.resource.compression.archive.FieldArchive implements com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named
A graph archive is a ZipArchive which is based on the support in java.util for ZipFiles. When a Graph is saved to a GraphArchive, the contents of its associated GraphStore is serialized with Kryo into a set of ZipEntry streams in the zip archive. You can see these streams with "unzip -v" on the command line. The graph archive can be loaded again at a later time by reading the serialized data.

This class handles the implementation details of saving and loading data from a graph archive. To save a graph, to a GraphArchive it is preferable to call Graph.save(GraphArchive). To load a graph, call load(Listener) or use the SmartGraphLoader, which supports loading graphs from all supported formats, including graph archives.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
